caption: Okay   I try to be fair the restaurant is very dark the employee for the most part are great. They fall flat in there patience with new customers is poor. Pay attention to regular local people. (Bread an butter) understand...... Claims had sand 😝😝😝😝😝 Steak was served on a rock new age I wouldn't of minded but it suck up all my steak dripping aka dam... lost flavor due to a rock Plate come on 3 three people 2 app 3 mains 7 drinks Equal 270 an 22% tip not worth it.  Just skip an ahead to Timpoine urbana They have a chef not a cook
Great food!
Super good food and service! Was pretty crowded but overall really good experience. Will definitely go back
We had a great experience at Nando! The food was excellent and the restaurant was adorable. Our service was very good too.

The food was amazing,  the service was so great and we loved the atmosphere.  Truly appreciated the complimentary prasecco and dessert for our anniversary.  Well definitely return before the next anniversary!
Nice atmosphere.  Mediocre food at a premium price.

Nando Milano is a gem. The wait staff is kind and attentive without being overbearing. The pasta is exceptionally tasty. I've ordered from their specials menu both times and loved each of my dishes. Even though you can easily get several dishes, just getting a single pasta dish will fill you up, so you don't have to always spend a lot of money. I love the atmosphere and the food is some of the best in CU.

Had a great time last weekend with my friends. We were celebrating my sister’s  birthday. If you love Italian foods, you’ll definitely love this place. The food was excellent & all the staff members were not only professional but also very friendly.  I Highly recommend!
Love the food always! Food takes a bit to get served but it's all worth it.
Loved the pasta and they have so many vegetarian options! Loved the service too! Highly recommend!
Good restaurant with some really good food a little on the pricey side as a heads up but has excellent service

One of the best Italian restaurants in the Midwest. The chef is amazing, the staples on the menu are fantastic and the specials are always dynamite. This place is a real treat and the staff is second to none! Highly recommend Nando Milano.

If you are looking for the best in quality and flavor, you won’t find anything better than Nando Milano.  In addition to all the wonderful dishes, the desserts are incredible.  Check it out you will not be disappointed

This is an amazing restaurant. From the moment you walk in you are transported to different time while being serenaded by the jazz greats. The food is pure ambrosia with authentic Italian cuisine. The ambiance is stellar with a top notch service staff. I highly recommended this restaurant to anyone visiting the Champaign area it is truly an experience your taste buds must have.

The waiters are really rude and lie to you about the pricing on FREE items like the bread, so that you don’t keep asking for more. Keep a look out for the bald white guy he’s the main one doing that. The bread was stale and they were very stingy about it. Overall extremely overrated and tacky. Will not be returning!
Amazing food and service. Will definitely visit again.
Arrived at 610 ordered put in at 630.  8 pm still no meal
One of my preferred places for tasty Italian food. filled me up in no time. had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again.
Great take on Italian cuisine served on a beautiful outdoor patio. Would definitely return.

We went on a Saturday, food was amazing! Server did a good job, but was very busy with tables inside, outside, and received little help from the rest of the wait staff.  The 2013 Montepulciano listed on the menu was actually a 2018, and the taste of wine I had beforehand was sent out in a 4 oz beer taster rather than a wine glass.  Coursing seemed a bit off and took quite a bit of time in-between each dish, the kitchen seemed fairly busy but the quality of the dishes was great once they arrived.  Overall a good experience with a few spots for improvement. We will definitely give it another go, but I was expecting a bit better for the $180 tab for two people.
Terrible pickup service. Waited over 30 minutes outside when they weren’t even busy.

The best of the best at Downtown, Champaign. The service is amazing. Not mentioning the food and wine. The Rigatoni Alla Beppe, Cioppino Toscano, the Sicilian wine... We went back three nights in a row. The chef even came out to say hi... That is huge. All the servers are amazing. Must-try in Campaign. I miss their homemade pasta so much...(ps... I rarely ate carb...)!

It’s Tuesday night and we sit down and it takes 20 min for the waiter to approach us for appetizers the bread is cold, now we order and our food takes close to an hour to get and the pasta is cold and it was not anything Italian it was more like ground beef stew and hard pasta with no flavor. So if you go make sure it’s not on a Tuesday night.

Our first experience at Nando Milano tonight was an exceptional 4 course meal.  Exceeded only by the service and ambiance of the restaurant.  Excellent job Nathaniel Thanks for the suggestions and your knowledge of the menu was on point.  Will definitely return and request Nathaniel.
Very good food. Everything was fresh and well prepared.

I was pleasantly surprised by the freshness of the seafood at Nando. All the food we had was superb and held the essential elements of being; fresh, balanced, and pleasing to the eye. The service was excellent, we had a charming and accommodating server. We will be returning to drink some wine in the evening, excellent restaurant.

We were in town for the night and the outdoor seating was wonderful. Great ambiance, wonderful food (seafood risotto and mahi) The server was very good and the rest of the staff were very pleasant and helpful. I will definitely eat there next time I am town.
Delicious food, all plates delicious! Variety too.
I had requested a vegetarian pasta specifically ordered off the menu. The Chef Alessio was just amazing. He prepared an awesome dish. The service is excellent
Excellent food. The Fresca Salad is out of the world.
Excellent food and excellent service.  All in all great experience.
Food, wine list, workers.....just amazing!!!!

I made a reservation at 9pm on Yelp. But when I arrived at the restaurant. The manager told me that I couldn’t have a seat and the kitchen was closed. The manager was rude and didn’t provide any explanation that why I can make a reservation since the restaurant was closed.

Perfect all around.  They made our anniversary evening very special. It was my first visit, but definitely will not be my last! -The food was the best Italian around and very authentic. The chef was amazing! -The service was second to none.  From the time we were seated throughout the entire night, the entire staff was attentive and kind but not overbearing!  I have a couple photos, but I did not take pictures of everything unfortunately. The special pistachio dessert was so good!

It was dark, crowded, noisy..food and wine was very good and the waitresses was excelent..patient on explaining things..and the flashing red lights on the fire truck at the restaurant across the street (false alarm) made it interesting to say the least.

My wife and I enjoyed a very pleasant date here. Food was clearly intentionally crafted and presented. Waiter was kind and attentive without being overbearing. The aesthetic of the environment was on point as well. The man who I believe may be the chef even greeted us on our way out asking how our experience was.
Great service and food

Had dinner there with the wife. Ambiance is nice and definitely gives you an old school Italian restaurant feel. Both of us had the try three menu that came with appetizer, main course and dessert. I had the octopus, seafood pasta and ricotta cheesecake. Octopus appetizer was amazing, pasta had the largest scallop I've seen yet on a dish in C-U and the cheesecake was delicious but not too heavy. Highlight for me were the negronis that were delicious. Downside was the price, (over 200 bucks), and the wife had the steak she requested at medium well that came out pretty pink. I would reccomend for a date night.
It was fab. Great food. Brilliant service. Would definitely wat there again 😁

Stopped for drinks and apps at the bar on Saturday night!  The bartender made my drink incorrectly TWICE, then still charged me full price.  I was simply asking for a Tito’s with club soda and lemon/lime garnish.  They kept adding lemonade and lime juice ugh — anyways, won’t be back!!  Paid $20+ for two drinks I didn’t even enjoy.
Get the dessert! (Had the prix fixe menu and was not disappointed)
Great Atmosphere. Authentic itilain dishes..
Beautiful place to eat. Staff was fast, friendly and knowledgeable.
Food not as great and long wait!!!
Excellent food and great service
The tables are to close to each other, it is way to dark and the food is bland not to mention very expensive.

Fantastic food from a great chef!  Comfort food favorites along with fine dining choices, cannot beat their authentic Italian cuisine.  Great wine selection!  Both food and wine sourced from best regions of the world.  Highly recommend!
Best traditional Italian restaurant in this area!.

Had a calamari appetizer on the servers suggestion. It was just ok. The sauce was like watered down buffalo. Sauce. My entree (crab and lobster ravioli with a single scallop) was absolutely delivious. However i could have eaten 3x what they gave me bc fat american. My date didnt finish her wild boar parpedelli which was good because i was still hungry. It was just ok tho too. My entree was good enough to come back but overall it did not live up to the hype.
I have always enjoyed the ambiance, food, and service.
It’s my go-to place in Champaign.
Good Good Good Good.
Nando Milano is special!!!! GOOD!!!!!!
Wow. Italiano Food. Specialeeeeeeeee! In Nando WE TRUST.
Never had anything bad on the menu. Excellent martinis as well.

This place is truly bizarre. The food is expensive, and the service is strange to the point of being silly. Our waiter tried to sell us every single menu item, and hardly took no for an answer. Then, we were charged for someone else's meal, which was basically double as expensive!
Massively overpriced. Quite absurd actually. The food and service certainly does not warrant the cost.
5 stars for interesting selections, taste, presentation, service and ambiance. For that - it’s worth the price . Thank you!
Food good and service excellent. A little different menu from most Italian restaurants.
Amazing italian food. Best restaurant in town.
Excellent Italian restaurant , wonderful service, drinks, and food. A winner Champaign is fortunate to have such an excellent restaurant downtown.

Went with family here for dinner and it was not only a delicious meal, but a lovely evening. The food was amazing and the waiter was nice and also very knowledgeable. Can't wait to go back to this place again when I'm in town!
Great service and ambiance with exquisitely delicious selections. Definitely going back there again.
overpriced.....way overpriced
Nando’s Is a true non fussy classic Italian bistro.  The blue chees gnocchis was a treat being subtle and fluffy like a cloud.
Nando Milano where great food, service, family all collide for an explosive Italian experience
Exotic Italian fine dining with excellent service.
The food never ceases to amaze me! Hands down my favorite place for Italian in Champaign.
The owner is rude. Doesn't pay his employees!!

This place is outstanding! Dario is a Prince and treats his customers with the same hospitality and culinary expertise as those who visit his restaurants in San Francisco and Chicago. Truly a special place with spectacular Italian cuisine.
Perfect Italian

Pleasant to sit outside, extremely noisy inside (something wrong with ceiling design). This is a branch of a Chicago restaurant, but significantly more expensive, plainly speaking overpriced. The food is very uneven, mostly oversalted. Too talkative and obnoxious owner. Biaggi remains the best Italian place in town.
Great meal outdoors.

Hailed as "the best Italian restaurant in the area", I have to say I'm disappointed. Kitchen timing was off (not everyone at the table got their food at the same time), the intentionally dim lighting did nothing to obscure the crumbling brick walls, but did serve to obscure the menu - a stained and water-damaged menu I might add. For the outrageous prices, I expected a lot better. The food was just "okay", but the only "truly authentic" food I was served was the olive oil.  So overall... very disappointed, and won't be returning.

We've been going here for many years and love it. The cocktails and food are fantastic and the location is wonderful, with great ambiance later at night. For Champaign it is a bit pricier, but they managed to turn a literal burnt-out husk of a building into a fantastic restaurant!
Love the desserts and wine here... Panna cotta is a must have...

This was my third time visiting Nandos. I always enjoy the experience. Their wait staff is well trained and managed. I actually feel like I'm getting a dining experience when I go here, not just having bored college kids ask me what I want. The lobster ravioli it's great, the lasagna was quite good, our appetizers were fantastic, especially the Brussels sprouts and seafood salad. On this visit the papardel and saltimbocca were both tasty. The carbonara was only so so. They have really good drinks, and they always have something new and interesting on the menu. You can tell there's a real chef at work here.
Always love coming to Nando Milano. Everything about this place is top-notch.
Wonderful place, delicious Italian cousin, this is the best place where i'm eating outside Italy... i'm Italian btw.... Dario and Alessio are amazing!
Hands down the best place to be and dine in downtown Champaign. Italian experience as his best
Wonderful food and service
Well I just love it here! the people. the food! oh my Tasty!
Delicious pasta dishes
Probably the best tasting I've had in Champaign. Josh, the waiter was super knowledgeable, friendly and accommodating. The sea bass was awesome!
Italian food and the scene here is super good. a favorite evening place of mine. nothing but enjoyable experiences here. the prices are well within reason for the quality.
Food was amazing as always, service was impeccable.

Very good food and the outside dining was fun. It's a more expensive type of restaurant, somewhat justified by the menu. The waiter was pretty slow to attend to my needs and was almost a little pretentious. He had an assistant however who was very good. I'm not into expensive wine, if you are, you'll like that too. I did think, based on the food that it was worth the effort and cost.

I don’t typically rate restaurants, but this was awful. We waited 15 minutes for any attention whatsoever. We were searching on our phones where to go because we were getting up to leave when the waiter finally came. We ordered everything all at once because we thought we will never get out of there. Food was so bland I couldn’t believe it. I’m a terrible cook and totally could have done better than this! I had the cod with polenta. $76 for two beers, a salad, cod, and about seven ravioli. Bread came after asking for it, but no olives. Waiter was inattentive. Don’t bother going here.

Worst dining experience ever! After being seated it took at least 15 min before anyone came to just get water.  Another 10 min before someone came to take a drink order.  We ordered food with drinks because we figured it would take forever for them to come back.  They said they’d bring us some bread and olives, which never came. Food was bland, no seasoning or flavor at all. No one ever came to ask how things were.  We were there almost 2 hours through this ordeal.  Shoulda just got up and walked out. Would NOT recommend this place.
Yummy 😋
Very good food, great wine and great service.
Food is always fabulous. Great outdoor dining.
Fantastic food.

Outstanding food and service. Brought a large group for a graduation celebration and every meal was excellent! Definitely recommend, although the noise level is high when the restaurant is busy. Would love to return.
Very accommodating. High price, food is decent.
Great atmosphere.  Delicious halibut.
Simply amazing!  Atmosphere was perfect, food delicious, treated like a king and queen.  Crab and Lobster ravioli is to die for.  The swordfish was spectacular.
Wonderful ❤️

(Translated by Google) This is a very fine Italian restaurant The atmosphere is very comfortable The service staff inside are very responsible And live piano performance 钢琴 Great for entertaining clients or sirs Also great for dating The price is on the high side but it is indeed a high quality restaurant.  (Original) 這是一間非常高級的義大利餐廳 氣氛非常舒適 裡面的服務人員都非常盡責 還有現場鋼琴演奏😂 很適合招待客戶或是長官 也很適合約會 價位偏高可是確實是高品質的餐廳😊
Inconsistent. They served raw meatballs the last time I went.

This place is great; tasty food, nice drinks, and wonderful service. They even have a couple gluten- free pasta options that they can swap into many of the pasta dishes. Chef Alessio makes some of the best food in town.

Such wonderful ambiance! The decor was high class, the music relaxing but yet a little upbeat to enjoy your entire time for dinner.  The service was 5-star and the owner was a wealth of information about the white wines we asked about and orhers, what an experience!  The food was 5-star as well. Cannot go wrong ordering anything here at Nando's.  Come savor the experience!
Very tasty and friendly staff!
Delicious. Elegant. Would come bac.
Mediocre Italian at best. Not returning.

(Translated by Google) Nice and quiet place. Good Italian cuisine. Typical and well prepared dishes. Congratulations to the cook  (Original) Posto bello e tranquillo.Buona cucina italiana. Piatti tipici e ben preparati. Complimenti al cuoco
Best Italian in the CU area after The Great I pasta was shut down. We've come here to celebrate quite a few times and have not been let down yet! Portions are good, food is great!
Always a great experience. Friendly staff. Plan on an hour or more here but you should not be in a rush at this type of place.
They really take great care of you.!
The Wagyu beef appetizer was excellent

Downtown Champaign has lacked a great Italian option for so long. I've been to Nando a half dozen times and every visit has been a treat. The food is phenomenal. The service is spectacular. Without being pretentious, they deliver a fine dining experience.

Awesome atmosphere and Italian experience!! Very good food and excellent service!  Come here with plenty of time. We were here over 2 hours but that was with 4 courses served! Perfect for a very special occasion or celebration. Hope to come back again...
Pricey, but excellent Italian food.

Tables are so close together that you knock over the drinks of your neighbor trying to get to your seat. My meal was not very good. But the wine selection is amazing. Atmosphere is very nice, but it's also loud because it is so crowded.
Terrific restaurant with an enjoyable atmosphere
Great food, and the restaurant is very cozy
Fantastic

I came here with my boyfriend for our first date and again for our first anniversary. The food is incredible, the staff is so friendly, and the place is beautiful. It's a perfect spot for a date. Save space for dessert because it is amazing and so worth it. My boyfriend and I come in just to have their semifreddo; it's that good. Absolutely love this place.
Excellent service and food. Best seafood risotto I have ever had

The atmosphere was amazing.  Staff very friendly.  Food was amazing but found it extremely expensive and very slow in recieving our drinks and food. We got there at 6:45, had reservations. Seated right away.  Took a while to be acknowledged and waited on. After be served and getting bill, we finally left at 10:00.
Solid menu, relaxing atmosphere. Wait for food was a little long, but worth it.
(Translated by Google) The best restaurant  (Original) El mejor Restaurante
The food is delicious!
The food was decent. The service was terrible.
Excellent food but too pricey
The white truffles we're amazing!
Pricey, but tasty. Didn't order $48 grouper, but did have $34 salmon. Next time we'll share salad and pasta al norma.
Good service, ok food

Our grandson surprised us and took us to our favorite restaurant ! As always superb ! My cod was delicious , the lamb was great and the chicken fantastic ! WAitstaff classy as was the owner'! Charmant
Upscale Italian in the heart of downtown Champaign! Delicious food and wine menu!

The eggplant pasta dish is the best!!! It has so much flavor and it even makes you close your eyes when you are eating it because it is so tasty! The almond brittle with chocolate sauce was amazing!!! We enjoyed everything we ordered!

Such a great restaurant! This was my first visit to Champaign and I was shocked to eat at an authentic Italian restaurant. The food was amazing and the service was even better. I highly recommend eating here if you are ever in the area. We had the meatball appetizer and I chose the Chicken Parmesan (pictured below). There were many other great choices, it was hard to choose!
Wonderful dinner this past Saturday night perfect service delicious food gracious staff    We will be back   Thanks Tamara and Lou
Great food. Only negative is that the place was way too cold.
Really nice Italian place, great food and very nice service
Excellent... Our favorite place when dropping our daughter off at school..

Every few months I making a mistake of going to a Nando Milano just yet to be disappointed again.  I'm not sure why do I have such mazochistic tendances.  Charming outside sitting and ambience probably have something to do with it. Besides it there is really nothing else. Food is mediocre at best (especially if you normally dine in NYC or Chicago). Service non existent.  Last dinner when I had gazpacho that tasted anything but it and waiting for my main course for 40 min without apologies of any sort put a final end in my relationship with this space.
Slòooow service due to the kitchen wait staff great and friendly portions to small for the price
The seafood ravioli — amazing! You won’t be disappointed. The tables are close together, so if that bothers you, just request a table a bit away from the others!
Great wine dinner!

Took my wife here for her birthday. The food was good, not great and the service was good. But the overall dining experience was lacking due to the  layout of the restaurant. If you are looking for a nice quiet dinner for two this is definitely not the place to go. Tables for two are lined up along the south wall of the restaurant with approximately 16" of separation between them. There are probably 12-14 tables total. We were seated in the middle of the row. Impossible to have a conversation due to the proximity of all the other diners. Based on reviews from friends and price of entrees on the menu, my expectation was a "fine dining" experience and this definitely fell short of that!
Excellent food. Sit at the bar if there's a long wait.
Delicious authentic Italian dishes.
This place quickly became our favorite restaurant in town. Pricing is above average for our area, but the food is obviously made entirely from scratch, and is the best in town.

Absolutely amazing authentic Italian food, in a wonderful, trendy but classy setting. The servers are always welcoming, and have never once let me down. A constantly changing menu of specials ensures you never grow bored of an already stellar regular menu. Without a doubt one of the best restaurants in Champaign Urbana.
Great place. I went without a reservation and was able to get a seat quickly. The owner was extremely friendly. The food was amazing. Best Italian in town.

The restaurant has a very nice setting on a pleasant street with lots of people walking and enjoying the downtown area. The interior is nicely decorated with a beautiful bar area. Unfortunately our experience was ruined by far too much waiting.  After waiting 40 minutes after our reservation time to be seated, we had to wait over 2 more hours for the food to arrive. Someone who I presumed to be owner came to the table but just shrugged his shoulders and made vague excuses along the lines of "we're busy" with no semblance of an apology. The wait staff was working hard, but didn't seem to be supported by the kitchen or the management.  I understand that setbacks happen. Maybe kitchen staff had an emergency and couldn't arrive to work. Maybe the food delivery truck didn't show up today. If there had been any sort of an attempt to explain  the delays and apologize I may have given this place a second chance. I don't expect complimentary food or drinks to make up for problems, but a little gesture like a bottle of house wine for the table along with an apology would have gone a long way too.
Great Italian food.

Good food. Takes a little longer since everything is made fresh in house. Nice ambiance with the owner being very active with the guests. Recommended calling in advance and making a reservation since it's not a big dinning room.
The food is just ok. But the price is really high. Plus, we wait a long time for the food.
Nice place , good food

Ok.  Good for Champaign but the service would  never make it in Chicago (we lived in the city for 20 years).  The food was good but at 8 pm on a Saturday they were out of 2 specials.  We ordered a 2nd bottle of wine but it took so long we refused it when it finally came.   4 for food. 2 for service.  3 total.
Awesome dishes and fantastoc service. Ive never had an experience like Nando.

Love the atmosphere, the management is incredibly kind and available to you. The food is beautifully presented and the quality is the best in Champaign - Especially for Italian and a date night - before the theater etc.
Dario never disappoints. The food is always spot on. Also one of the better wine selections in CU.
Fantastic service, food and atmosphere. Highly recommended. If you are looking for a memorable experience and have a passion for good food, this is the place for you.
A full-course dinner Italian restaurant. Services are excellent and food was even better. Try chef special menu. Sea bass, Lamb or seafood pasta all the best.
They serve 5 olives. 5. Not more not less. Crab/lobster ravioli was way undercooked and took forever to come out I didn't want to wait so ate the 5 shells of ravioli and left.

The food here is great! We went on a Wednesday night and the service was a little slow for a restaurant of this caliber. I've been here before though with outstanding services so maybe they were just having an off night. Either way, the food is amazing!
The oysters were not shucked properly but tasted fine. Enjoyed a Bee's Knees for my pre-dinner cocktail. Nice atmosphere for a quiet dinner.
Delicious Italian fine dining!!! Outstanding, albeit occasionally inconsistent, service. Excellent management. Definitely worth it to take your SO here for a nice evening.

On the high end expense wise I got one drink, no meal. My wife got one drink and a salad. They don't have any salads with meat, so she had a meat added to it. Just for the two drinks and salad it came to $65. Which is pricy, even for down town. I didn't really like the menu options, so would not come here again, but I will say it is a very high class environment, and very well maintained atmosphere/decor.

This restaurant is a combination of a traditional and modern Italian restaurant. The menu includes the dishes  known well in the US in addition to those are not - wild boar from northern Italy and octopus from the south. A lively  ambiance and very good service top it off.
Great food, great service. A true 5 star experience!
It would be 5 if it wasn't for the portions. Just a bit too small for my taste. Otherwise, the environment is great, nice lighting, authentic, nice servers. Overall, enjoyed it and would come again!

Came with a party of 12 people. Reservations were made at 1 pm the day of.  It took the waiter 30 mins to take the order and 1:25 mins  to get the food.  Food was sloppy, waiter was inattenative, and non responsive to requests.  When spending over 140 for 3 people I would expect all around better service and food.
Here from Jersey and this food was as good as you would get in New York City. No kidding. Small menu and everything made from scratch. Highly recommend loster ravioli with a scallop
It was awesome!! I highly recommend it!!

Nando Milano is THE place to go for fine dining in Champaign. Delicious Italian cuisine, warm atmosphere, attentive and professional staff will have you never wanting to leave.  Dario, the owner, oversees everything like a hawk and personally makes sure your experience is nothing short of excellence.  He embraces every guest as family and will have you looking forward to your next visit.  A+

If you're looking for a fine dining experience, this is the place to go! You will spend about 2 hours here from the time you sit down to the time you get up to leave. If you're trying to get your food and eat and leave within a reasonable time, then this is not your place! However, the food is very good and the service is excellent! Our server was extremely knowledgeable about the menu and made great suggestions for us!
Great authentic Italian, good service and nice atmosphere.  Desserts are fantastic and the drinks are good.  Great date place and a solid go to any night of the week.
The food was good, our waiter was fair,  the background music was to loud and it was hard to carry on a conversation.  Prices were high.
Wonderful food and great recommendations!
Food is some of the best Italian food in Chsmpaign, IL
Love eating out side!! Great food and service

The waiter was from Italy.  Very pleasant.  My wife enjoyed her meal.  I got the Chef's special which was veal.  It was a hunk of bone with fat surrounding it.  Very little meat.  I said to the waiter " It was mostly fat" he says "That is the way its supposed to be, gives it flavor".  Living in central Illinois, raising cattle to eat for myself and close friends, I know the difference between fat that flavors and fat that should be disposed of.  They should stick to the pasta.

Nothing special about that place I could literally do any of those dishes at home and the prices are ridiculous for the amount of food you get. Do yourself a favor go to next door(cowboy monkey) and get yourself some pork tacos and a nice margarita.
There was nothing special to me about the food and it was very much overpriced.  A memorable meal is one where I savor every bite and I did not experience that at Nando Milano's in Champaign.

We were greeted right at the door. Very friendly, attentive and knowledgeable staff. Food was superb (especially the pasta). Decor and ambiance are very nice too. I was pleasantly surprised that our waiter asked about food allergies and about the timing of our meal (when certain items should be brought out). Very thoughtful, professional and considerate of all that goes into your dining experience.
Pushy staff trying to upsell, overcooked pasta beyond belief, otherwise it is one of nicer places in Champaign
Always great here

A wonderful family owned authentic Italian restaurant.... The owners are from Italy they greet you with a smile!  The staff is professional, knowledgeable and fun!  Great place to relax and spend un-rushed time with your friends!  Great Bartender too! Dan

We went here for a birthday celebration. Nandos easily has the most authentic Italian food in Central Illinois. The pasta is handmade. The seafood is incredibly fresh. Our experience was wonderful. This is our new favorite restaurant for special occasions!
Entrees are very good, and the service nice.Desserts are okay. Iwould  have liked pasta to be 'al dente' :)
This place is outstanding! I highly recommend this spot if you want Italian it's amazing!!!
We decided to visit for our anniversary and we treated very well by Carlos. He was very helpful at assisting us to decide. On the pricy side but would definitely visit again.
Not my cup of tea

So far I've been here twice. Pros: I've thoroughly enjoyed both entrees I've gotten (one was a seasonal pasta dish with butternut squash, the other was the gnocchi alla sorrentina). The gnocchi were the lightest, fluffiest gnocchi I've ever had. Cons: The food was good, but I wish they'd been a little clearer on the menu. I was trying to avoid dairy (not a life threatening allergy, so I didn't want to make an issue of it), so I tried to pick something that didn't have cheese or cream listed on the menu.  My gnocchi came smothered in melted cheese which was less than ideal. The other major con is that the place can get pretty loud. It  can be kind of hard to hear your companions.

Excellent authentic Italian Restaurant . The food is always wonderful as is the attention from the owner ,Dario and his brother Allesio . The Octopus special last night was a true delight . We always have a fabulous meal when we go. Excellent wine list and deserts as well !!!

A lot of reviewers don't get this place.  If you are looking for a quiet meal, this is not for you.  But if you are looking for some amazing cooking, look no further!  The chef's specials are always incredible and be sure to save room for dessert!!!
Knowledgeable staff. Great food. Nice atmosphere. Reasonable prices.
Brautiful deco. Very comfortable. Fabulous Food
Best restaurant in Champaign, IL. Food was phenomenal. Service was precise. The atmosphere was fit for any occasion. Large, or small groups would be okay. Probably not the best place to bring kids.

It was a really great, authentic experience. Carlo was an awesome server and our table of 7 felt completely taken care of. Food was wonderful but don't expect a ton of food. But portion size was just about perfect.
Great food and ambiance

Easily one of the best restaurants in Champaign-Urbana, outstanding in its food, staff, and atmosphere. I have yet to dine there without being personally greeted by the owner, and I have yet to select anything on the menu that hasn't been among the best dishes I've had.
One of the best restaurants in CU.  The specials range from good to amazing so it's worth going again if you didn't love it the first time.
Wonderful food and great service. Always feel like family when we visit Nando Milano.

I highly recommend this place to anyone looking to get in touch with their inner italian self. I had a very well crafted Fettuccine Bolognese. And as funny as it was to say that it tasted just as good. I recommend saying "stronzo" very frequently when here as it shows how cultured you can be. Overall a very classy restaurant for a very classy stronzo.  **UPDATE** Restaurant was incredibly slow and that became very irritating after 3 hours of bding couped up in the restaurant. Gratzi.
9-28-16.  Way over priced. Very long wait. Very noisy. Gnocchi Nonna was horrible.  Wanted lasagna but they ran out.   Won't be back.
It was really loud and we didn't enjoy the evening.  The food was OK, but not worth the super high prices.  The lady we had as a server was really good though.

Good Italian food. Authentic. Gluten free pasta is available.  A little noisy, but nice interior design. I think one or two of the tables should be removed from the dining room because the table by the entrance is the worst. Good waiters. Be prepared for a slow dinner. Time to converse with friends and family. Nothing is rushed in this place. Casual attire. Suburban Chicago prices.
Expensive, but it was some of the best food I have ever had

Nando is the best restaurant in Champaign-Urbana, and to the person who compared the bolognese to canned sauce, you obviously have no clue because it's wonderful, and I make my own. And have you had any and all of their desserts? Amazing!! Love!
I had the bolognese, not bad by US standards, but well below Italian standards. The sauce tasted like canned sauce, nothing like home made bolognese. Canned sauce bought in the UK tastes better.
Lovely restaurant, attentive staff and amazing food provide an all around great experience!!  Yummy :)

Excellent Italian restaurant. I recommend the gnocchi, they have a great soft and smooth texture and taste great. Skip the tiramisu for dessert, too dry. Entree prices are fair, salad and wine prices are high (the salads are good though).
Excellent. Authentic. Great service.  Experience was great. Fine dining but not pretentious. Quite expensive but an excellent choice for special occasions.
Fantastic food. Get the truffles. Authentic Italian food. Everything is made fresh so take your time but it is well worth the wait. We will be back often.
